# Event generation information file (only for testing purposes)
#
# Access task needs stopping and then running manually with extra parameter to do automatic events generation based on this file.
# Stop accesstask either by issuing API command OR running this "/etc/init.d/access stop" command in terminal on controller.
# Then run accesstask using command mentioned below from controller terminal:
#       # /mnt/apps/bin/accesstask /mnt/apps/data/config/CfgFile stderr 0 autoevent
# Running using above command will run access which reads/parse this file at location "/mnt/apps/data/config/GenEventsInfo" and generate events
# through event-logger and when done exit. So no accesstask will be running after automatic event generation. So either use API to
# restart accesstask OR run this "/etc/init.d/access restart" command in terminal on controller
#
#
# Start of event generation file:
#
# Here each single entry line represent a single type and parameter event. 
# Same event type can be repeated multiple times again on new line with different parameters.
#
#
# Fields required are:
#
# Count: number of times that event needs to be generated
# Delay: Is delay (in milliseconds) between each event generation
# Task: Task code (number, only few supported for now: 1, 2)
# Type: Event type code (number, should be valid and same as defined in 2.3.1 API document)
# Message: Message Type/ID (number, only few are supported for now: 1 - 6, 27, 41, 44)
# Additional Fields: Extra fields for event, should follow what is in API document otherwise unexpected application behviour
# 

# Count  Delay     Task  Type  Message   Additional-Fields ...... 
# [Repeat 10 times with 0 ms dealy] Access task, Below is Grant access example for interface 0, reader 0 and unique-id 5
    10     0         2    20      1      0 0 5 
# [Repeat 5 times with 1000 ms dealy] Access task, Deny access example with unique-id 3
     5     1000      2    27      1      0 1 3
# [Repeat 10000 times with 0 ms dealy] Identification task, host lookup example with hexcardpin and nbits
   10000   0         1    40      2      0 0 00C1C600 32
# [Repeat 100000 times with 0 ms dealy] Access task, Deny access wrong pin 
   100000   0         2    29      3      0 1 7 1234

